ai-kv17.10:0.4_0: The account of the ninth garden of the Buddha
ai-kv17.10:1.4_0: He does not enter the best, the two, the best, the best, the best, the tamed, the best, the undefeated, the foremost, the best, chief, highest, and finest of the world.
ai-kv17.10:1.6_0: The Buddha’s dispensation. He is the best of those who can’t be tamed, paid, bestowed on the best seat, the finest lady, the best seat, the bestowed on the best seat, the bestowed on the best seat, going to be told, the best of the best.
ai-kv17.10:2.4_0: There is a Buddha equal to him—
ai-kv17.10:2.6_0: there’s no-one else who does not exist in nothing.
ai-kv17.10:2.7_0: There is no one equal to the Buddha
ai-kv17.10:2.8_0: And he should be told with wisdom.
ai-kv17.10:4.2_0: the Buddha is best and confined.
ai-kv17.10:4.3_0: That is the best of those who have reached the highest goal.
ai-kv17.10:5.3_0: The Buddha’s gift is very fruitful.
ai-kv17.10:5.4_0: Only what is given to the Buddha is not to be spoken of in the fruit of the Buddha.
